25. irasci celerem: Horace’s quick temper may possibly be referred to in Carm. 111. 9, 22 improbo iracundior Hadria ,- and more directly in Sat. 11. 7, 35. It is exaggerated in Sat. 11. 3, 323 non dico horrendam rabiem.

27. Decembres: Suetonius gives the date of Horace's birth as sexto idus Decembris. The year of his birth is fixed by Carm. 111. 21, 1 o nata mecum consule Illanlio, and by Epod. 13, 6 tu vina Torquato move consule pressa meo to the consulship of

L. Manlius Torquatus and L. Aurelius Cotta in B.c. 65, a date which Suetonius also gives. <
